ers-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERising%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20sticky%20inflation%20were%20two%20of%20the%20big%20macro%20themes%20that%20defined%202025.%20According%20to%20Gapen%20and%20his%20team%2C%20companies%20opted%20to%20decrease%20hiring%20and%20reduce%20staffing%20to%20avoid%20raising%20prices%20earlier%20in%20the%20year%20as%20tariff%20pressures%20kicked%20in.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20though%2C%20the%20tides%20had%20shifted%2C%20and%20companies%20across%20industries%20were%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraising%20prices%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eagain%2C%20citing%20tariffs%20as%20the%20primary%20catalyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%20says%20that%20this%20may%20be%20the%20key%20to%20avoiding%20widespread%20layoffs%20in%20the%20coming%20year.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20tariff%20pass-through%20to%20final%20consumer%20prices%20will%20have%20been%20completed%20at%20that%20point%2C%20assuming%20the%20administration%20does%20not%20push%20tariff%20policy%20further%2C%26quot%3B%20Gapen%20said.%20%26quot%3BOn%20net%2C%20our%20outlook%20assumes%20inflation%20firms%2C%20profitability%20is%20largely%20restored%2C%20and%20the%20economy%20avoids%20layoffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economist%20added%20that%20his%20team%20doesn't%20expect%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20implement%20new%20tariffs%20as%20the%202026%20midterm%20elections%20approach.%20Yet%2C%20the%20analysts%20also%20emphasize%20that%20they%20don't%20think%20companies%20are%20done%20raising%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20maintains%20its%20baseline%20view%20that%20the%20existing%20tariffs%20will%20push%20core%20inflation%20to%203%25%20early%20in%202026%2C%20with%20signs%20already%20being%20seen%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20consumer%20goods.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMonthly%20rates%